House Prices Analysis

2024-08-10

Introduction

In this analysis, we will explore house price trends across different states over time. We will use the house_prices.rda dataset to create visualizations and reshaped data for further insights.

library(ggplot2)
library(tidyr)
library(dplyr)
## 
## Attaching package: 'dplyr'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     filter, lag
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     intersect, setdiff, setequal, union
# Load the dataset
load('~/Downloads/DATA/house_prices.rda')
ggplot(house_prices, aes(x = date, y = house_price_index, color = state)) +
  geom_line() +
  facet_wrap(~ state) +
  scale_x_continuous(
    breaks = c(1980, 2000, 2020),
    labels = c("80", "00", "20")
  ) +
  labs(
    x = "Year",
    y = "House Price Index",
    title = "Trends of House Price Index Over Years for Each State"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),
    legend.position = "none"
  )

house_reshaped <- house_prices %>%
  gather(key = "measure", value = "value", house_price_index, unemploy_perc, -state, -date)

head(house_reshaped)
## # A tibble: 6 × 5
##   date       state   house_price_perc measure           value
##   <date>     <chr>              <dbl> <chr>             <dbl>
## 1 1976-01-01 Alabama           0.0404 house_price_index  37.1
## 2 1976-02-01 Alabama           0.0518 house_price_index  37.8
## 3 1976-03-01 Alabama           0.0593 house_price_index  38.3
## 4 1976-04-01 Alabama           0.0596 house_price_index  38.6
## 5 1976-05-01 Alabama           0.0557 house_price_index  38.7
## 6 1976-06-01 Alabama           0.0536 house_price_index  38.8
ggplot(house_reshaped, aes(x = date, y = value, color = measure)) +
  geom_line() +
  facet_wrap(~ state) +
  scale_x_continuous(
    breaks = c(1980, 2000, 2020),
    labels = c("80", "00", "20")
  ) +
  labs(
    x = "Year",
    y = "Value",
    title = "Trends of House Price Index and Unemployment Percentage Over Years for Each State",
    color = "Measure"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)
  )
